layout: article
title: Messaging
description: Send push, email, and SMS from Appwrite with the same overall flow. Connect providers such as APNs, FCM, or email and SMS services, organize recipients with topics and targets, then send using the Messages API.
back: /docs
---

Appwrite **Messaging** helps you reach users on push, email, and SMS without wiring a different integration for each channel from scratch. Use it for receipts and alerts, login codes, or newsletters - whatever your product needs to send.

You group people with [topics](/docs/products/messaging/topics), store how to reach them with [targets](/docs/products/messaging/targets), and connect real providers under [providers](/docs/products/messaging/providers) (for example Apple or Google for push, Mailgun or Twilio for email or SMS). Your app usually calls [messages](/docs/products/messaging/messages) to send; Appwrite routes to the right channel.

You can add [Functions](/docs/products/functions) in front of sends if you want extra steps first (custom templates, throttling, or pulling rows from [Databases](/docs/products/databases)).

