# How messaging fits together {% #how-messaging-fits-together %}

**Providers** hold the credentials Appwrite uses to talk to Apple, Google, email services, SMS carriers, and similar backends. Your app should not embed those secrets.

**Topics** are lists of who should get a broadcast-style message. **Targets** link a user (or device) to an email, phone number, or push token for a given provider. **Messages** are what your code creates; Appwrite takes care of routing and the channel-specific details where supported.

Use [Auth](/docs/products/auth) so you know who each recipient is. Use [Functions](/docs/products/functions) if you want to change the payload, load rows from [Databases](/docs/products/databases), or add [Storage](/docs/products/storage) links before a message goes out.
